Key Match Events: Karl-Anthony Towns returned from a one-game absence with 26 points, 15 rebounds, and six assists.
OG Anunoby had 24 points and eight rebounds for the Knicks.
Mikal Bridges added 21 points and Josh Hart had 20 points, eight rebounds, and eight assists for the Knicks.
Jalen Brunson finished with 12 points and 10 assists despite shooting 3 for 14.
Cam Johnson scored 22 points for the Nets.
The Knicks beat their city rivals for the eighth straight time.
Brunson made a jumper with 9:11 left in the third quarter, contributing to a 12-4 spurt that extended a two-point lead to 76-66.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Knicks held Cam Thomas to 16 points on 4-for-11 shooting after he scored a season-high 43 points on Friday.
The Knicks completed a two-game weekend sweep of the Brooklyn Nets.
